.TH "pci_p2pmem_alloc_sgl" 9 "pci_p2pmem_alloc_sgl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_p2pmem_alloc_sgl \- allocate peer-to-peer DMA memory in a scatterlist
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct scatterlist *" pci_p2pmem_alloc_sgl
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *nents "  ","
.BI "u32 length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
the device to allocate memory from
.IP "nents" 12
the number of SG entries in the list
.IP "length" 12
number of bytes to allocate
.SH "RETURN"
NULL on error or \fIstruct scatterlist\fP pointer and \fInents\fP on success
